## Literature Workflow

Three commands for managing citations and literature:

| Task | Command | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Find papers | `/research-scientist:search-literature` | `search-literature adipose mortality` |
| Add from DOI | `/research-scientist:add-citation` | `add-citation 10.1016/j.jacc.2023.01.001` |
| Read PDF | `/research-scientist:read-paper` | `read-paper ~/Downloads/paper.pdf` |

**Workflow for adding a new reference:**
1. Search: `/research-scientist:search-literature [topic]` → find relevant papers
2. Add: `/research-scientist:add-citation [DOI]` → generates BibTeX
3. Cite: Use `[@citationkey]` in paper.md

